<br>
As for lord bob, 2 things basically went wrong:<br>
<br>
1 - CH rotation failed.  The 2nd CH didn't hit and we didn't have enough spam healers to make up the difference....was close but not quite.<br>
<br>
2 - Poor Sara is going to have to watch her feet on all of these....she lagged out to the point that the slow/cripple didn't get cast.  Jedc was able to cast the slow but it was resisted.<br>
<br>
Our next attempt at lord bob will make a couple of changes...<br>
<br>
1 - A bit more practice on CH rotations coming into it.  2 clerics can do a 7 sec rotation...3 can do 5.  We tried to do 5 second rotation with 2 and the math doesn't work.<br>
<br>
2 - More coordination with all enchanters/shammies for the debuffs.  Basically you win this fight if you debuff (slow and cripple him) and lose if you don't.  All debuffers will be pretargeted and facing walls or feet.  1 person tashes...shammy malo/malase....bard oos...full resist debuff as quick as possible ... then ALL chanters / shammy / bard / beastlord start chaining slow till one lands...then same with cripple.  At that point bards should start singing Katta's to debuff his dex even farther.  Once that's done he's owned.<br>
<br>
Jedc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub144.ezboard.com/baltusdomini.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xtinctioneq>Xtinction EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#330000>(10/30/02 6:39:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub144.ezboard.com/faltusdominifrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dragonslayers</span><hr size=1> with two clerics C3'ed(which they will be before we try this again if I have to drag jedc by the ear to the planes and get him xp to lvl 60 I will) we should be able to handle the rotation.  I"ll admit last time I was way off on my cast timing, which caused Raivene to go down and the sh*t storm started....and slow is the key, the first few CH's are tough to get on just right, but once slow comes in its easy to keep the MT healed from there. <p>Whitepaw - 52 Wood Elf Ranger<br>
