<br>
The initial problem with the rotation is that for a 5 second CH rotation you have to have 3 clerics...when you add cast time plus recovery time you can cast 1 CH per 13 secs or so...so a 5 sec rotation (A ch hits every 5 seconds) requires 3 clerics to do. <br>
<br>
Now once he's slowed and crippled (and this is true of a lot of mobs...like statue for example) a single cleric can heal the MT.<br>
<br>
On these type of mobs we need to focus on 3 things:<br>
<br>
Initial CH rotation...we just need practice is all.<br>
<br>
Slow - We have to get them slowed<br>
<br>
Dex Debuff - Cripple, Katta, Rogue poisons - The lower the dex the less flurry, rampage and other nasty procs come to bear.<br>
<br>
